During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders announced that Sean Spicer has resigned from his position as White House Press Secretary. She read a statement from President Trump thanking Spicer for his work and wishing him continued success. Sanders also announced that Anthony Scaramucci has been appointed as the new White House Communications Director. Scaramucci gave a brief statement and answered questions from reporters. He expressed his respect for Spicer and his commitment to working together with the press. The press briefing also touched on other topics such as the President's meeting with survivors of the attack on the USS Arizona, the signing of an executive order for a defense industrial base assessment, the reauthorization of the Department of Homeland Security, and the ongoing efforts to repeal and replace Obamacare.